# openhands-actions-test



For all changes to actual application code (e.g. in Python or Javascript), add an appropriate test to the testing directory to make sure that the issue has been fixed.

git_patch:
diff --git a/src/hello_world.go b/src/hello_world.go
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..50cfb13
--- /dev/null
+++ b/src/hello_world.go
@@ -0,0 +1,7 @@
+package main
+
+import "fmt"
+
+func main() {
+    fmt.Println("Hello World")
+}
\ No newline at end of file
diff --git a/src/hello_world_test.go b/src/hello_world_test.go
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..8eca658
--- /dev/null
+++ b/src/hello_world_test.go
@@ -0,0 +1,21 @@
+package main
+
+import (
+    "testing"
+    "os/exec"
+    "bytes"
+)
+
+func TestHelloWorld(t *testing.T) {
+    cmd := exec.Command("go", "run", "hello_world.go")
+    var out bytes.Buffer
+    cmd.Stdout = &out
+    err := cmd.Run()
+    if err != nil {
+        t.Fatalf("Failed to run hello_world.go: %v", err)
+    }
+    expected := "Hello World\n"
+    if out.String() != expected {
+        t.Errorf("Expected %q but got %q", expected, out.String())
+    }
+}
\ No newline at end of file

history.diff:
--- /workspace/src/hello_world_test.go
+++ /workspace/src/hello_world_test.go
@@ -0,0 +1 @@
+package main
@@ -1,0 +3,19 @@
+import (
+    "testing"
+    "os/exec"
+    "bytes"
+)
+
+func TestHelloWorld(t *testing.T) {
+    cmd := exec.Command("go", "run", "hello_world.go")
+    var out bytes.Buffer
+    cmd.Stdout = &out
+    err := cmd.Run()
+    if err != nil {
+        t.Fatalf("Failed to run hello_world.go: %v", err)
+    }
+    expected := "Hello World\n"
+    if out.String() != expected {
+        t.Errorf("Expected %q but got %q", expected, out.String())
+    }
+}
